                                Grant</persName> as the first U.S. Consul to <placeName
                                xml:id="scotland">Scotland</placeName> on July 14, 1798 in
                                <placeName xml:id="leith">Leith</placeName>. The U.S. Consulate
                            crossed into <placeName xml:id="edinburgh">Edinburgh</placeName> in
                            1854, but it moved back to Leith in 1861. The Consulate finally settled
                            back in Edinburgh in 1883, where it remains today.</p>
